From: Michael Chan <mchan@broadcom.com>
Date: Sun, 29 Jul 2012 19:15:44 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 085/105] tg3: Fix race condition in tg3_get_stats64()
Patch-mainline: v3.6-rc1
Git-commit: 0f566b208b41918053b2e67399673aaec02dde5d
References: bnc#790588 FATE#313912

Spinlock should be taken before checking for tp->hw_stats.

Signed-off-by: Michael Chan <mchan@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Nithin Nayak Sujir <nsujir@broadcom.com>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c |    6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c
@@ -12665,10 +12665,12 @@ static struct rtnl_link_stats64 *tg3_get
 {
 	struct tg3 *tp = netdev_priv(dev);
 
-	if (!tp->hw_stats)
+	spin_lock_bh(&tp->lock);
+	if (!tp->hw_stats) {
+		spin_unlock_bh(&tp->lock);
 		return &tp->net_stats_prev;
+	}
 
-	spin_lock_bh(&tp->lock);
 	tg3_get_nstats(tp, stats);
 	spin_unlock_bh(&tp->lock);
 
